### Register a new customer
POST http://localhost:8080/v1/customers
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "John Doe",
    "email": "john.doe@mail.com",
    "phoneNumber": "47999999999",
    "cpf": "12345678901"
}

### List customers with pagination
GET http://localhost:8080/v1/customers?page=0&size=10

### Get a customer by ID
GET http://localhost:8080/v1/customers/1

### Update a customer
PUT http://localhost:8080/v1/customers/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "John Doe",
    "email": "john.doe@mail.com",
    "phoneNumber": "48999999999",
    "cpf": "12345678901"
}

### Deactivate a customer
PATCH http://localhost:8080/v1/customers/1/deactivate

### Activate a customer
PATCH http://localhost:8080/v1/customers/1/activate

### Try to create a new customer with an existing email (should return an error)
POST http://localhost:8080/v1/customers
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Jane Doe",
    "email": "john.doe@mail.com",
    "phoneNumber": "47988888888",
    "cpf": "10987654321"
}

### Try to create a new customer with an existing CPF (should return an error)
POST http://localhost:8080/v1/customers
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Jane Doe",
    "email": "jane.doe@mail.com",
    "phoneNumber": "47988888888",
    "cpf": "12345678901"
}

### Try to create a new customer with missing required fields (should return an error)
POST http://localhost:8080/v1/customers
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "paul.senior@mail.com"
}

### Try to create a new customer with too long name (should return an error)
POST http://localhost:8080/v1/customers
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "This is a very long name that exceeds the maximum allowed length of 255 characters. It should trigger a validation error when trying to create a new customer in the system.",
    "email": "jim.cavizel@mail.com",
    "phoneNumber": "47977777777",
    "cpf": "10987654322"
}

### Try to create a new customer with invalid email format (should return an error)
POST http://localhost:8080/v1/customers
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Emily Blunt",
    "email": "emily.blunt-at-mail.com",
    "phoneNumber": "47966666666",
    "cpf": "10987654323"
}

### Try to create a new customer with invalid phone number format (should return an error)
POST http://localhost:8080/v1/customers
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Michael Fassbender",
    "email": "michael.fass@mail.com",
    "phoneNumber": "invalid-phone-number",
    "cpf": "10987654324"
}

### Try to create a new customer with invalid CPF format (should return an error)
POST http://localhost:8080/v1/customers
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Scarlett Johansson",
    "email": "scarlett.johansson@mail.com",
    "phoneNumber": "47955555555",
    "cpf": "invalid-cpf"
}

### Try to get a non-existing customer (should return an error)
GET http://localhost:8080/v1/customers/999